German Companies Well Equipped for Decline, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-08-31T06:24:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/german-companies-well-equipped-for-decline-handelsblatt-says.html
German companies are well equipped
for any potential economic decline as the “positive trend with
credit-worthiness and insolvency is unbroken,”  Handelsblatt 
said, citing Volker Ulbricht, chief executive officer of debt
collection and business information agency Creditreform.  To contact the reporter on this story:
